      "id": "save-004",
      "title": "Track spending for 7 days to find quick wins",
      "readingTime": "6 min",
      "tags": ["budget", "tracking", "habits"],
      "body": "If saving feels impossible, start with 7 days of tracking. A short tracking period is less stressful than “tracking forever,” and it still reveals your biggest leaks.\n\nStep 1: For 7 days, write down every spend (even small coffee). Use notes, a spreadsheet, or any budget app.\n\nStep 2: At the end of the week, group spending into categories: food, transport, shopping, subscriptions, entertainment, and “random.”\n\nStep 3: Circle the top 3 categories where you spent more than expected. These are your quick wins.\n\nStep 4: Choose one small change for each.\n- Food: plan 2 simple meals at home.\n- Subscriptions: cancel 1 unused service.\n- Shopping: add a 24-hour waiting rule.\n\nStep 5: Repeat once per month. You don’t need daily tracking forever. Monthly check-ins are often enough.\n\nTip: Don’t judge yourself while tracking. Tracking is not punishment. It’s information.\n\nOutcome: you’ll usually find at least 50–150 EUR/month in expenses you can reduce without hurting your quality of life."
