      "id": "save-006",
      "title": "Cancel or downgrade subscriptions in a clean way",
      "readingTime": "5 min",
      "tags": ["subscriptions", "budget", "quickwins"],
      "body": "Subscriptions are easy to forget because they are small and automatic. But 5–10 small subscriptions can become a serious monthly cost.\n\nStep 1: List all subscriptions (streaming, apps, cloud storage, gym, delivery memberships). Check bank statements for the last 30 days.\n\nStep 2: Mark each one as:\n- “Must keep” (high value)\n- “Maybe” (rarely used)\n- “Cancel” (not used)\n\nStep 3: Cancel the “Cancel” group immediately. Don’t postpone it.\n\nStep 4: For “Maybe,” downgrade plans or pause for 1–2 months. Many services let you stop and return later.\n\nStep 5: Set a subscription review reminder every 3 months.\n\nTip: If a service is valuable, keep it—but choose one or two that truly matter. You don’t need everything.\n\nOutcome: people often save 20–80 EUR/month with zero lifestyle pain."
