      "id": "save-007",
      "title": "Build a ‘no-loan’ buffer for predictable big expenses",
      "readingTime": "6 min",
      "tags": ["sinkingfund", "planning", "safety"],
      "body": "Many ‘unexpected’ expenses are actually predictable: gifts, annual insurance, car repairs, school costs, holidays. When you don’t plan for them, you might use credit.\n\nSolution: create a sinking fund (a planned savings pot for known expenses).\n\nStep 1: List 5–10 expenses you know will happen in the next 12 months.\nExamples: car maintenance, dentist, birthdays, travel, yearly subscriptions.\n\nStep 2: Estimate the cost for each.\n\nStep 3: Divide each cost by the number of months left until you need it.\nExample: 300 EUR in 6 months → save 50 EUR/month.\n\nStep 4: Put that amount into a separate savings “bucket.”\n\nStep 5: When the expense happens, you pay it with your sinking fund, not credit.\n\nResult: fewer emergencies, fewer loans, and a calmer budget."
