      "title": "Reduce food costs without ‘eating boring’",
      "readingTime": "7 min",
      "tags": ["food", "budget", "quickwins"],
      "body": "Food is one of the biggest monthly costs. The goal is not to eat less—it’s to waste less and plan better.\n\nStep 1: Choose 2–3 simple base meals for the week (pasta, rice bowls, soups, salads). Repeat is okay.\n\nStep 2: Make a short shopping list and buy only what you need for those meals.\n\nStep 3: Use a “snack rule”: buy snacks once per week, not daily.\n\nStep 4: Reduce delivery. Start with one small change: delivery only once per week.\n\nStep 5: Cook in batches. Cooking once can cover 2–3 meals.\n\nBonus tip: If you often throw away food, you’re paying for garbage. Plan smaller portions and use leftovers.\n\nResult: saving 50–200 EUR/month is common with a few realistic changes."
