      "readingTime": "6 min",
      "tags": ["systems", "budget", "safety"],
      "body": "A simple money system can prevent overspending without constant tracking. The idea: separate your money by purpose.\n\nBasic setup:\n1) Spend account: daily purchases.\n2) Bills account: rent, utilities, debt minimums.\n3) Savings account: emergency and goals.\n\nStep 1: On payday, move money to Bills first.\nStep 2: Move money to Savings second.\nStep 3: The rest stays in Spend.\n\nWhy it works: your Spend account shows the real amount you can use. Bills and Savings are protected.\n\nTip: If you only want two accounts, combine Bills and Savings into one “Protected” account and keep Spend separate.\n\nResult: less stress, fewer surprises, and clearer decisions."
