      "readingTime": "5 min",
      "tags": ["habits", "basics", "automation"],
      "body": "‘Pay yourself first’ means saving before you start spending. It is one of the most effective habits because it changes the order of your decisions.\n\nStep 1: Decide on a small amount you can save every month (even 10–25 EUR).\n\nStep 2: Save it immediately when money arrives.\n\nStep 3: Treat it like a bill. You don’t skip rent, so you don’t skip your savings.\n\nStep 4: Increase it when your income increases.\n\nTip: If you struggle with consistency, start with a weekly transfer instead of monthly.\n\nOutcome: your savings grow automatically, and you stop relying on “willpower” at the end of the month."
