      "id": "save-015",
      "title": "Plan debt and savings together (so you don’t burn out)",
      "readingTime": "7 min",
      "tags": ["debt", "planning", "safety"],
      "body": "If you focus only on debt, you can feel exhausted. If you focus only on savings, debt can become expensive. A balanced approach is usually more sustainable.\n\nStep 1: Pay minimums on all debts first (always).\n\nStep 2: Build a small emergency buffer (even 300–500 EUR). This prevents new debt from surprises.\n\nStep 3: After that, split extra money: part to debt, part to savings.\nExample: 70% extra to debt, 30% to savings.\n\nStep 4: Use clear milestones:\n- Debt reduced by 10%\n- Emergency buffer reaches 1 month\n\nStep 5: Review every month. Adjust the split if your life changes.\n\nTip: Consistency is more important than perfect strategy. A plan you can follow for 6–12 months wins.\n\nOutcome: you reduce debt while still building security, which makes your financial progress calmer and more stable."
